The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Nov. 5: Punjab National Bank and Indian Bank today hiked their interest rates on non-resident deposits. PNB has hiked the rates on NRE term deposits by 30 basis points. Indian Bank has increased its rates for NRE deposits by 25-30 basis points with effect from November 4. PNB has raised the rates on foreign currency non-resident deposits by 24-31 basis points, while Indian Bank has increased its by 23-38 basis points.

 New Delhi, Nov 5: Union petroleum ministry and the ministry of panchayati raj have set up a joint committee to push forward the implementation of bio-diesel programme through the panchayati raj institution and with greater participation of public sector oil companies such as Indian Oil Corporation. 

 New Delhi, Nov. 5: National Thermal Power Corporation will complete 30 years of existence this month. The corporation is now venturing into power trading activity. ?The company has plans to acquire parallel distribution licenses in different parts of the country for this,? said a statement from NTPC.




